		<!-- message -->
		<div>People who parse a lot say ripostes are a small proportion of incoming damage from mobs while tanking.<br />
<br />
Basic rule is avoid it anywhere you don't want to give the mob a chance to get the occasional free hit on you.<br />
<br />
So when tanking heavy hitting named you're not sure you can survive, you might turn attack off and use spell aggro only.  And when raiding heavy hitters, avoid the front of the mob so you don't pick up the odd 2K riposte and create a nuisance for your group healer.<br />
<br />
Oh and 1 handers are supposed to be worse for ripostes than 2 handers like Slein says.</div>
