		<div>There are times I forget to turn off attack when the mob goes into riposte mode, but whether I'm using a one hander or a two hander doesn't seem to matter much since generally our weapons are slow.  However, a dual wielding class (including pets) can be affected greatly and lose hp quickly.<br />
<br />
Side note, when I think my group isn't too alert or are chatting a lot, what I do when the mob enrages is back up.  The mob follows me and the pets end up behind the mob... and the dual wielders go out of melee range.</div>
