		<div>Mobs will Enrage when they reach low health (usually around 11% or under). It doesn't multiply the damage they deal, what actually happens is that the mob gets an automatic riposte on all attacks that hit him from the front. Basically, against any mob that Enrages, you should stand behind it, and you will be safe. Be careful though if you choose to continue attacking from behind an Enraged mob, as the main tank will have switched attack off, so you might get aggro (though as SKs are not exactly a high DPS class, that's not something we have to worry about  <img src="images/smilies/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="roll eyes (sarcastic)" class="inlineimg" /> ) You'd be surprised how many level 65s still eat Enrage death on raids, even in Elementals....<br />
