		<!-- message -->
		<div>I remember back when mobs in Umbral Plains would enrage and it was most players' first experience with it. At that point I played a Druid and it was very possible to "force an enrage" if all the nukers in the group let loose at the wrong time. They removed that and people got lazy again and everyone went back to hitting atk and going AFK.<br />
<br />
On raids you've got a shitload of DPS pumping out, you've got lag, you've got people shoved all around you preventing you from backing up. Good rule of thumb is to turn off attack earlier than 9%. My personal "oh shit enrage" % is usually about 12% or so, sometimes more depending on the mob and the level of DPS. That gives me enough time to turn off attack and back up out of melee range. Doing this a bit early also affords you a wonderful ringside seat from which to laugh at those who got chewed to death in seconds.<br />
<br />
When enrage gets close, you have a lot of people stopping what they are doing and backing off. This raises the chance that you're going to be the one getting a face full of rage, and the chance the mob will turn if the MA loses agro completely. Rogues *really* love when this happens and it's usually a good idea to not laugh at them when it does or you'll never get your corpse dragged again.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
